The paper presents a novel algorithm for multicopter trajectory planning that leverages depth images from an onboard camera. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the algorithm uses a pyramid-based spatial partitioning method, which involves computer vision techniques, indicating that the paper could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The algorithm is also capable of quickly evaluating thousands of candidate trajectories, which suggests that it could be related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves navigation of a quadcopter, which is a control system, indicating that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
